2 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
3 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 12 O.S. 2021, Section 1804, is
4 amended to read as follows:
5 Section 1804. A. Prior to commencement of any dispute
6 resolution proceedings, the disputing parties shall enter into a
7 written consent which specifies the method by which the parties
8 shall attempt to resolve the issues in dispute.
9 B. The written consent shall be in a form prescribed by the
10 Administrative Director of the Courts and shall include the
11 following:
12 1. The rights and obligations of all parties pursuant to the
13 provisions of the Dispute Resolution Act; and
14 2. The confidentiality of the proceedings.
15 C. If the parties agree to have the resolution reduced to
16 written form, a copy shall be provided to the parties.
17 D. An alternative dispute resolution proceeding conducted
18 pursuant to Section 13 of this act shall not be subject to the
19 requirements of this section.
20 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 311.5 of Title 36, unless there
22 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 A. On a quarterly basis, beginning March 31, 2027, each insurer
24 authorized to write personal and commercial property insurance in
Req. No. 3789 Page 4

1 this state shall file with the Insurance Department a supplemental
2 report with information regarding personal and commercial
3 residential property insurance policies in this state. Such report
4 shall:
5 1. Be filed electronically in the manner and form prescribed by
6 the Insurance Commissioner in accordance with any instructions from
7 the Department;
8 2. Include separate information for personal lines property
9 policies and for commercial lines property policies; and
10 3. Include the following information for each zip code,
11 monthly:
12 a. the total number of policies in force at the end of
13 each month,
14 b. the total number of policies canceled,
15 c. the total number of policies not renewed,
16 d. the total number of new policies written,
17 e. the total written premium,
18 f. if such insurer is actively writing policies,
19 g. the number of policies that exclude wind coverage,
20 h. the number of new claims open during each month,
21 i. the number of claims closed during each month,
22 j. the number of claims pending at the end of each month,
23 and
24
Req. No. 3789 Page 5

1 k. the number of claims in which either the insurer or
2 insured invoked any form of alternative dispute
3 resolution.
4 B. Supplemental quarterly reports filed with the Commissioner
5 pursuant to this section shall be treated as working papers and
6 documents pursuant to subsection F of Section 309.4 of Title 36 of
7 the Oklahoma Statutes.
8 C. The Insurance Commissioner may use supplemental quarterly
9 reports to assist in determining whether a market conduct
10 examination or investigation of an insurer should be conducted. For
11 the purposes of completing a market conduct examination of any
12 company pursuant to Sections 309.1 through 309.7 of Title 36 of the
13 Oklahoma Statutes, the Commissioner may use supplemental quarterly
14 reports or amendments or addendums to such reports to assist in
15 determining compliance with the laws of this state and rules adopted
16 by the Commissioner.
17 D. The Commissioner may, after notice and opportunity to be
18 heard for an insurer, subject such insurer to a civil penalty of up
19 to One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00) for each occurrence of a
20 violation of the provisions of this section, along with any other
21 penalties set forth in state law.
