4 SECTION 5. AMENDATORY 36 O.S. 2021, Section 942, is
5 amended to read as follows:
6 Section 942. Any insurance carrier that issues motor vehicle
7 liability or collision insurance policies in this state shall not
8 establish or apply premium rates, increase premium rates, cancel a
9 policy, or refuse to issue or renew a policy, based on any traffic
10 record maintained by the Department of Public Safety which
11 including, but not limited to, traffic complaints, traffic
12 citations, or other legal forms of traffic charges and accident
13 reports, that covers a period of time more than three (3) years
14 prior to the date the insurance carrier makes a determination to
15 take any such action; provided, however, those offenses that are
16 provided for in subsection C of Section 941 of this title and the
17 offense of reckless driving as provided for in Section 11-901 of
18 Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes may be considered by an insurance
19 carrier for a period of not more than five (5) years.
20 SECTION 6. AMENDATORY 36 O.S. 2021, Section 943, is
21 amended to read as follows:
22 Section 943. A. No insurance carrier who issues motor vehicle
23 policies in this state shall use traffic complaints, traffic
24 citations, or other legal forms of traffic charges as a basis for
Req. No. 3789 Page 9

1 canc ellation of a motor vehicle insurance policy, increasing premium
2 rates for a motor vehicle insurance policy, or refusing to issue or
3 renew a motor vehicle insurance policy, where the insured was:
4 1. the insured was acquitted Acquitted of the charge;
5 2. the insured was arrested Arrested and no charges were filed;
6 or
7 3. the insured was arrested Arrested and the charges were
8 dismissed.
9 B. No insurer shall cancel, refuse to renew, or otherwise
10 terminate a motor vehicle policy that has been in effect more than
11 forty-five (45) days solely because the insurer filed a first claim
12 against the policy. Nothing in this subsection shall be construed
13 to prevent the cancellation, nonrenewal, or other termination for:
14 1. Nonpayment of premium;
15 2. Discovery of fraud or material misrepresentation in the
16 procurement of the insurance or with respect to any claims
17 submitted;
18 3. Offenses set forth in subsection C of Section 941 of this
19 title;
20 4. Offenses set forth in Section 11-901 of Title 47 of the
21 Oklahoma Statutes; or
22 5. A determination by the Insurance Commissioner that the
23 continuation of the policy would place the insurer in violation of
24 the insurance laws of this state.
