5 SECTION 13. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
6 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1250.4a of Title 36, unless
7 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
8 A. For purposes of this section, “claim” means any dispute
9 between an insurer and a policyholder relating to a material issue
10 of fact other than a dispute:
11 1. Where the insurer has a reasonable basis to suspect fraud;
12 2. When there is no coverage under the policy based on
13 presented facts as to the cause of loss;
14 3. Where the insurer has a reasonable basis to believe that the
15 policyholder has intentionally made a material misrepresentation of
16 fact that is relevant to the claim, and the entire request for
17 payment of a loss has been denied on the basis of the material
18 misrepresentation;
19 4. When the policyholder suffers no actual monetary or property
20 loss, based on presented facts;
21 5. When a claim is outside the time frames prescribed in
22 applicable law; or
23 6. When a claim has been paid in full prior to any mediation
24 session held pursuant to this section.
Req. No. 3789 Page 31

1 B. The Insurance Commissioner’s dispute resolution program
2 shall assist consumers and insurance companies effectively,
3 economically, and fairly, and timely resolve disputes with persons
4 or entities subject to the jurisdiction of the Insurance
5 Commissioner and related to insurance or service warranty claims.
6 Such dispute resolution period shall be subject to the provisions of
7 Sections 1801 through 1813 of Title 12 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
8 C. Mediation may be requested only by the policyholder as a
9 first-party claimant, a third party as an assignee of the policy
10 benefits, or the insurer.
11 D. Mediation shall be voluntary except that insurers shall
12 participate in any mediation requested by a first-party claimant or
13 third-party claimant, as assignee of the policy benefits that:
14 1. Involves an insurance claim under a residential or
15 commercial residential or automobile insurance policy; and
16 2. Has not commenced civil litigation relating to the claim to
17 be mediated.
18 E. A claim shall not be eligible for mediation unless it has
19 first been submitted and fully processed through the Insurance
20 Department’s consumer complaint program.
21 F. All parties to the mediation shall negotiate in good faith
22 to resolve the dispute and shall have the authority to immediately
23 settle the claim. The dispute shall not be required to be resolved
24 in mediation. If a written settlement is reached and the
Req. No. 3789 Page 32

1 poli cyholder is not represented by an attorney, the policyholder
2 shall have three (3) business days in which the policyholder may
3 rescind the settlement unless such policyholder has cashed or
4 deposited any check, draft, or other payment made to the
5 policyholder as a result of the settlement. If a settlement
6 agreement is reached and is not rescinded, it shall be binding as a
7 release of all specific claims presented in the mediation
8 conference.
9 G. 1. A mediation conference shall be held as scheduled by the
10 dispute resolution program coordinator. Upon application by any
11 party for continuance, the program coordinator shall, for good cause
12 shown or if neither party objects, grant a continuance and shall
13 notify all parties of the date and place of the rescheduled
14 conference. Good cause shall include:
15 a. severe illness, injury, or other emergency that could
16 not be controlled by the party and could not
17 reasonably be remedied by the party prior to the
18 conference by providing a replacement representative,
19 or
20 b. the necessity of obtaining additional information,
21 securing the attendance of a necessary professional,
22 or the avoidance of significant financial hardship.
23 2. If the policyholder demonstrates to the mediator the need
24 for expedited mediation conference due to an undue hardship, the
Req. No. 3789 Page 33

1 conf erence shall be conducted at the earliest date convenient to all
2 of the parties and the mediator. Undue hardship shall be
3 demonstrated if holding the conference on a non-expedited basis
4 would interfere with or contradict the treatment of a severe illness
5 or injury, substantially impair a party’s ability to assert their
6 position at the conference, result in significant financial
7 hardship, or other reasonably justified grounds.
8 H. An insurer shall be deemed to have failed to appear if the
9 insurer’s representative lacks authority to settle the full value of
10 the claim. The authority to settle a claim shall include the
11 ability to disburse the full settlement amount within ten (10) days
12 of the conclusion of the conference. The insurer shall produce at
13 the conference a copy of the policy and shall bring the entire
14 claims file to such conference.
15 I. Any violation of this section by an insurer shall subject
16 the insurer to discipline including a civil penalty not more than
17 Ten Thousand Dollars ($10,000.00), in addition to any other
18 penalties provided by law.
19 J. The Commissioner may promulgate rules necessary for the
20 enforcement of the provisions of this section.
